column13:
Our server was AWESOME. A totally fun guy. So much so, that I wanted to get all 5-year old on him and say, &#34;Hey, can we be friends?&#34;

The tuscan bean salad was delish. Like lick-the-plate-clean delish. The chicken parm, however? It fell flat. Don&#39;t get me wrong, I still ate it. It certainly wasn&#39;t BAD. But it was just standard. And when you really impress me with the appetizer, you set a high bar for the entree - it just didn&#39;t meet it. 

Tuesdays are 1/2 off Long Islands, if you&#39;re into that kind of thing. And I would suggest visiting on a Tuesday anyway, even if you&#39;re not into that kind of thing. We were seated right away, got our food quick, and our drinks were refilled like nobody&#39;s business.
